name: Aqua (Danone)
description: Danone is a multinational food-products corporation headquartered in Paris, France. It was founded in Barcelona, Spain, in 1919 by Isaac Carasso. The company's original product was yogurt, which was sold under the brand name "Danone". Danone's product portfolio includes a variety of dairy and plant-based products, bottled water, baby food, and medical nutrition. Some well-known brands under Danone's umbrella include Activia, Actimel, Danonino, Danette, evian, and Alpro. The company is a major player in the dairy industry, offering a range of yogurts, dairy desserts, and fermented dairy products. In recent years, Danone has also expanded its presence in the plant-based market with products like plant-based yogurts and beverages.

3. Customer Experience Awards 2022: OVAL, Kompas Gramedia's customer experience and marketing platform, was awarded in the "Best Data Activation" category for its data-driven approach to enhancing customer engagement.
4. Bank Sampah program: Kompas Gramedia's waste management initiative, Bank Sampah, has been recognized for its positive environmental impact and its role in promoting circular economy practices.
5. Integration with SDGs: Kompas Gramedia has integrated the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) into its business strategy and operations, demonstrating its commitment to social responsibility and sustainable development.
6. Education initiatives: Kompas Gramedia has established numerous educational institutions, including the Kompas Gramedia School of Journalism, to nurture future generations of journalists and media professionals.
7. Community engagement: Kompas Gramedia actively engages with local communities through various programs, such as book donation drives and cultural events, promoting literacy, education, and cultural appreciation.

name: Teh Botol Sosro
description:
Teh Botol Sosro, Indonesia's iconic bottled tea beverage, has been a beloved part of Indonesian culture for over 50 years. With its signature refreshing taste and unwavering commitment to quality, Teh Botol Sosro has become a household name, synonymous with authentic Indonesian tea enjoyment.

Teh Botol Sosro's success lies in its unique blend of Indonesian black tea and natural ingredients, resulting in a distinctively flavorful and refreshing beverage. The brand has consistently maintained its high standards of quality, ensuring that each bottle delivers the same authentic taste that has captivated generations of Indonesians.
value:
1. Pioneer of RTD Tea in Indonesia: Teh Botol Sosro is widely recognized as the pioneer of RTD tea in Indonesia, introducing the concept of bottled iced tea to the country in 1974. This innovative move revolutionized the beverage industry and set the stage for the widespread popularity of RTD tea in Indonesia.
2. Market Leader and Brand Loyalty: Teh Botol Sosro has consistently maintained its position as the market leader in the Indonesian RTD tea industry, achieving a market share of over 60%. The brand enjoys strong brand loyalty among Indonesian consumers, thanks to its consistent quality, refreshing taste, and affordable price point.
3. Product Innovation and Expansion: Over the years, Teh Botol Sosro has consistently introduced innovative product variants to meet the evolving needs of consumers. This includes introducing new flavors, launching smaller bottles for on-the-go consumption, and expanding into new product categories like dairy-based tea drinks.
4. International Recognition and Awards: Teh Botol Sosro has garnered numerous international awards for its quality, innovation, and marketing efforts. These include the Top Brand Award, the Indonesia Best Brand Awards, and the Master Brand Award.
5. Sustainability and Social Responsibility: Teh Botol Sosro is committed to sustainability and social responsibility, implementing programs to reduce its environmental impact and support local communities. This includes using recyclable PET bottles, promoting recycling initiatives, and partnering with community organizations.
6. Cultural Impact and Symbol of Indonesia: Teh Botol Sosro has become deeply embedded in Indonesian culture, serving as a ubiquitous beverage at gatherings, celebrations, and daily life. The iconic green bottle and the brand's tagline "Ayo, Minum Teh!" ("Come, drink tea!") have become synonymous with refreshment and Indonesian culture.

name: Gojek
description: Gojek, Southeast Asia's leading on-demand, multi-service tech platform, has revolutionized the way people live, work, and connect. Founded in 2010 with a focus on solving Jakarta's ever-present traffic problems, Gojek started as a call center with a fleet of only 20 motorcycle-taxi drivers (ojek). Today, Gojek has expanded to over 50 cities across Indonesia and Vietnam, offering a comprehensive range of services, including transportation, food delivery, payments, logistics, and many more. With a mission to create and scale up positive socio-economic impact, Gojek has empowered millions of drivers and merchants, fostering inclusive economic growth and transforming the lives of Indonesians and Vietnamese.
value:
1. Rapid Growth and Expansion: Gojek has experienced phenomenal growth since its launch, becoming Indonesia's first unicorn startup and expanding its reach to over 200 cities in Indonesia and other Southeast Asian countries. The company has amassed a massive user base of over 200 million, solidifying its position as a dominant player in the on-demand and mobility sectors.
2. Diversification and Expanding Service Offerings:Gojek has continuously expanded its service offerings beyond its core ride-hailing business, introducing a wide range of services catering to various needs, including food delivery, grocery and parcel delivery, payments, and entertainment. This diversification has transformed Gojek into a comprehensive super app, addressing the everyday needs of its users.
3. Technological Innovation and Cutting-edge Solutions: Gojek has invested heavily in technology to enhance its platform and provide users with innovative solutions. The company has developed proprietary algorithms, machine learning capabilities, and data analytics tools to optimize operations, personalize experiences, and enhance user satisfaction.
4. Social Impact and Community Engagement: Gojek has demonstrated a commitment to social impact and community engagement, supporting micro-entrepreneurship, empowering women, and contributing to financial inclusion. The company has launched various programs to help small businesses grow, provide opportunities for women in underserved communities, and promote financial inclusion among its users.
5. Recognition and Awards: Gojek has received numerous accolades and recognitions for its innovation, growth, and contributions to the Indonesian economy and society. The company has been ranked among the "Top 50 Companies That Changed the World" by Fortune and has won numerous awards for its technology, social impact, and overall business performance.
6. Merger and Acquisitions: Gojek's growth has been fueled by strategic mergers and acquisitions, acquiring key players in the on-demand and fintech sectors to expand its reach and enhance its service offerings. These acquisitions have strengthened Gojek's position as a leading player in the digital economy.
7. Global Expansion Plans: Gojek has ambitious global expansion plans, aiming to replicate its success in other Southeast Asian countries and beyond. The company has established operations in Vietnam, Thailand, and Singapore, and it is exploring opportunities to expand into other markets.

name: Grab
description: Grab, Southeast Asia's leading superapp, has become the go-to platform for everyday services across the region. With a comprehensive suite of offerings, including ride-hailing, food delivery, e-payments, and more, Grab has transformed the way people live, work, and connect in over 400 cities across eight Southeast Asian countries. Founded in 2012 as a taxi-hailing app, Grab has evolved into a superapp that caters to diverse needs and preferences, simplifying daily tasks and enhancing convenience for millions of users.
value:
1. Pioneering Superapp Model in Southeast Asia: Grab is widely recognized as the pioneer of the superapp model in Southeast Asia, seamlessly integrating a wide range of services into a single platform. This includes ride-hailing, food delivery, grocery and parcel delivery, payments, and other on-demand services, making it a one-stop shop for users' daily needs.
2. Market Leadership and Regional Expansion: Grab has established itself as the market leader in Southeast Asia's on-demand economy, operating in over 400 cities across eight countries. The company has amassed a user base of over 185 million and a network of over 8 million driver-partners and merchants, solidifying its dominance in the region.
3. Diversification and Expanding Service Offerings: Grab has continuously expanded its service offerings beyond its core ride-hailing business, venturing into various sectors to meet the evolving needs of its users. This includes financial services, healthcare, entertainment, and enterprise solutions, transforming Grab into a comprehensive super app with a wide-reaching impact.
4. Technological Innovation and Cutting-edge Solutions: Grab has consistently invested in technology to enhance its platform and provide users with innovative solutions. The company has developed proprietary algorithms, machine learning capabilities, and data analytics tools to optimize operations, personalize experiences, and enhance user satisfaction.
5. Social Impact and Community Engagement: Grab has demonstrated a commitment to social impact and community engagement, supporting micro-entrepreneurship, empowering women, and contributing to financial inclusion. The company has launched various programs to help small businesses grow, provide opportunities for women in underserved communities, and promote financial inclusion among its users.
6. Recognition and Awards: Grab has received numerous accolades and recognitions for its innovation, growth, and contributions to the Southeast Asian economy and society. The company has been ranked among the "Top 50 Companies That Changed the World" by Fortune and has won numerous awards for its technology, social impact, and overall business performance.
7. Public Listing and Market Valuation: Grab achieved a significant milestone in 2021 by becoming the first Southeast Asian unicorn to list on the Nasdaq stock exchange. The company's initial public offering (IPO) raised over US$4.5 billion, valuing Grab at over US$40 billion at the time.
8. Sustainability Initiatives: Grab has implemented various sustainability initiatives to reduce its environmental impact and promote eco-friendly practices. This includes introducing electric vehicles, promoting carpooling, and encouraging reusable packaging.
9. Future Outlook and Expansion Plan: Grab continues to expand its reach and explore new opportunities, aiming to become the leading digital economy platform in Southeast Asia. The company is actively pursuing partnerships, expanding into new markets, and developing new services to maintain its competitive edge.

name: OVO
description: OVO, Indonesia's leading digital payment platform, has revolutionized the way people make transactions. Founded in 2017, OVO has quickly gained widespread adoption, becoming a ubiquitous part of Indonesian daily life. With a user-friendly interface, seamless integration with various merchants and services, and a commitment to security and convenience, OVO has empowered millions of Indonesians to embrace cashless transactions and simplify their financial interactions.
value:
1. Rapid Growth and Market Leadership: OVO has experienced rapid growth since its launch, becoming the leading digital payment platform in Indonesia with over 40 million users. The company has expanded its reach to over 200 cities across Indonesia, facilitating seamless cashless transactions for a wide range of services.
2. Diversification and Expanding Service Offerings: OVO has transformed from a pure-play digital payment platform to a comprehensive fintech ecosystem, offering a suite of financial services beyond payments. This includes mobile banking, insurance, wealth management, and investments, making OVO a one-stop shop for financial needs.
3. Strategic Partnerships and Ecosystem Expansion: OVO has forged strategic partnerships with leading brands and organizations across various sectors, including telecommunications, retail, e-commerce, and financial institutions. These partnerships have expanded OVO's reach and enabled integration with everyday transactions.
4. Technology Innovation and Cutting-edge Solutions: OVO has invested heavily in technology to provide users with innovative and secure payment experiences. The company has developed proprietary payment gateways, fraud prevention systems, and data analytics tools to enhance user experience and security.
5. Social Impact and Community Engagement: OVO has demonstrated a commitment to social impact and community engagement, promoting financial inclusion and economic empowerment. The company has launched initiatives to provide financial literacy education, support micro-entrepreneurship, and promote financial inclusion among underserved communities.
6. Recognition and Awards: OVO has received numerous accolades and recognitions for its innovation, growth, and contributions to the Indonesian economy and society. The company has been ranked among the "Top Digital Payment Startups in Indonesia" by KPMG and has won numerous awards for its technology, social impact, and overall business performance.
7. Collaborations and Global Expansion Plans: OVO has collaborated with international partners to expand its reach beyond Indonesia. The company has partnered with global payment giants like Mastercard and Visa to facilitate cross-border payments and expand its global presence.
8. Future Outlook and Ambitious Plans: OVO continues to expand its reach and explore new opportunities, aiming to become the leading fintech ecosystem in Indonesia and Southeast Asia. The company is actively developing new products and services, expanding into new markets, and forging strategic partnerships to maintain its competitive edge.

name: Unilever
description: Unilever, a global consumer goods corporation, has been a household name for over 90 years, offering a wide range of products that enhance everyday life. With a commitment to sustainability, innovation, and social responsibility, Unilever has established itself as a leading force in the consumer goods industry. From personal care products like Dove and Axe to food brands like Knorr and Lipton, Unilever's products are used by millions of people around the world.
value:
1. Industry Leadership and Global Presence: Unilever is one of the world's largest consumer goods companies, with a portfolio of over 400 brands spanning personal care, home care, and food & refreshment categories. The company operates in over 190 countries, reaching billions of consumers worldwide.
2. Innovation and Product Leadership: Unilever has a rich history of innovation, developing groundbreaking products that have revolutionized consumer behavior and improved people's lives. Some of the company's iconic brands, such as Dove, Axe, Rexona, and Lipton, are testaments to its commitment to innovation and product excellence.
3. Sustainability Pioneer and Environmental Stewardship: Unilever has been a pioneer in sustainability, setting ambitious goals and making significant progress towards reducing its environmental impact. The company has committed to sourcing 100% of its agricultural raw materials sustainably by 2030 and to halving its greenhouse gas emissions by 2030.
4. Social Responsibility and Community Engagement: Unilever is committed to making a positive impact on society, supporting social causes and empowering communities around the world. The company's Sustainable Living Plan focuses on four key areas: sourcing sustainable ingredients, reducing environmental impact, empowering consumers to make sustainable choices, and supporting community development.
5. Corporate Citizenship and Recognition: Unilever has received numerous accolades and recognitions for its social responsibility and environmental leadership. The company has been ranked among the "World's Most Ethical Companies" by Ethisphere for many years and has won numerous awards for its sustainability initiatives.
6. Employee Engagement and Inclusive Workplace: Unilever is committed to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace where employees can thrive and be their best selves. The company has implemented various initiatives to promote diversity, equity, and inclusion, and has been recognized as a top employer for women and LGBTQ+ individuals.
7. Ethical Business Practices and Transparency: Unilever is committed to conducting business ethically and transparently. The company has developed a strong corporate governance framework and publishes regular sustainability reports that track its progress towards its ambitious goals.
8. Future Outlook and Sustainable Growth: Unilever is committed to long-term sustainable growth, driven by innovation, sustainability, and social responsibility. The company is investing in new technologies, developing sustainable products, and expanding its reach to underserved markets, aiming to create value for its customers, shareholders, and society.

name: Nestle
description:
Nestlé, a global food and beverage company, has been shaping the world's culinary landscape for over 150 years. With a presence in 188 countries, Nestlé's iconic brands, such as Nescafé, KitKat, and Maggi, are household names, synonymous with quality and innovation. Driven by its purpose of enhancing quality of life and contributing to a healthier future, Nestlé continuously pushes the boundaries of food and beverage science, creating products that are both delicious and nutritious.

Nestlé's commitment to sustainability is deeply ingrained in its operations, from sourcing ingredients responsibly to minimizing its environmental impact. The company strives to create shared value, not only for its consumers but also for the communities it serves and the planet as a whole. With a focus on nutrition, health, and wellness, Nestlé is dedicated to making a positive impact on the world, one sip and bite at a time.
value:
1. Product Innovation and Brand Recognition: Nestlé has consistently demonstrated its prowess in product innovation, introducing iconic brands that have become household names worldwide. From the nutritious Nescafé coffee to the beloved KitKat chocolate bar, Nestlé's products have captured the hearts and taste buds of consumers across generations.
2. Global Expansion and Diversification: Nestlé has expanded its operations to become a truly global company, with a presence in over 180 countries and a portfolio of over 2000 brands. This global reach has allowed Nestlé to tap into diverse markets and consumer preferences, making it one of the world's largest food and beverage companies.
3. Commitment to Sustainability: Nestlé has recognized the importance of environmental sustainability and has taken proactive steps to reduce its environmental impact and promote regenerative food systems. The company has implemented initiatives to improve water stewardship, promote sustainable packaging, and support sustainable farming practices.
4. Focus on Nutritional Advancement: Nestlé has played a significant role in improving nutrition globally, particularly through its infant nutrition products and fortified foods. The company has invested in research and development to create nutritious and affordable food options that address global malnutrition challenges.
5. Corporate Social Responsibility: Nestlé has demonstrated a commitment to corporate social responsibility, prioritizing ethical sourcing practices, promoting diversity and inclusion, and supporting community development projects. The company has been recognized for its efforts in these areas.
6. Employee Engagement and Talent Development: Nestlé is known for its commitment to its employees, investing in training, development, and career advancement opportunities. This focus on talent has helped the company attract and retain top talent, contributing to its long-term success.
7. Financial Performance and Market Leadership: Nestlé has consistently achieved strong financial performance, demonstrating its ability to adapt to changing market conditions and consumer demands. The company holds a leading position in the global food and beverage industry, with a strong brand presence and a diversified portfolio.

name: Roma Sari Gandum
description:
Roma Sari Gandum is a popular Indonesian biscuit brand known for its wholesome and nutritious products. Introduced in 1977, Roma Sari Gandum has become a staple in many households, offering a delicious and satisfying snack that is also good for you.

Made with whole wheat flour and enriched with essential vitamins and minerals, Roma Sari Gandum biscuits provide a healthy dose of fiber and nutrients. They are also low in fat and cholesterol, making them a guilt-free indulgence. With a variety of flavors to choose from, including classic plain, chocolate sandwich, and fruit-filled varieties, Roma Sari Gandum caters to diverse tastes and preferences.

Roma Sari Gandum biscuits are not only tasty and nutritious, but they are also convenient and portable. They come in individually wrapped packs, making them ideal for on-the-go snacking or school lunches. Whether you're looking for a quick bite to satisfy your hunger or a nutritious snack to fuel your day, Roma Sari Gandum biscuits are a perfect choice.
value:
1. Market Leadership in Wheat Flour Production: Roma Sari Gandum has established itself as the leading wheat flour producer in Indonesia, capturing a substantial share of the market. The company's high-quality flour products are widely used in bakeries, food processing industries, and households across the country.
2. Commitment to Quality and Innovation: Roma Sari Gandum has consistently prioritized quality and innovation in its production processes. The company has implemented stringent quality control measures and actively invests in research and development to enhance its product offerings.
3. Expanding Product Range and Diversification: Roma Sari Gandum has expanded its product range beyond traditional wheat flour to include a variety of specialized flour products catering to specific needs. This diversification has broadened the company's customer base and strengthened its market position.
4. Strong Distribution Network and Brand Recognition: Roma Sari Gandum has established a robust distribution network that effectively reaches all corners of Indonesia. The company's brand is well-recognized and trusted by consumers, making it a preferred choice for wheat flour products.
5. Commitment to Sustainability and Social Responsibility: Roma Sari Gandum has demonstrated its commitment to sustainability by implementing environmentally friendly practices throughout its operations. The company also supports social responsibility initiatives, contributing to the well-being of communities in which it operates.
6. Financial Performance and Market Growth: Roma Sari Gandum has achieved consistent financial growth and expansion, reflecting its strong market position and effective business strategies. The company has played a significant role in the development of the Indonesian food industry.
7. Contribution to Indonesian Food Industry: Roma Sari Gandum's success has been instrumental in enhancing the quality and variety of wheat flour products available in Indonesia. The company's contributions have supported the growth of the bakery and food processing industries and have improved access to quality food for Indonesian consumers.

name: Nabati
description:
Nabati Group is an Indonesian food and beverage company founded in 2002 with a focus on fast-moving consumer goods (FMCG), particularly food and soft drinks. The company initially started as a small-scale home-based snack food business. Over the years, Nabati has grown into a prominent player in the Indonesian FMCG industry, with a diverse portfolio of brands and products.

Nabati's commitment to quality and innovation has been instrumental in its success. The company continuously develops new and exciting products that cater to the evolving tastes and preferences of Indonesian consumers. Nabati's flagship brands, such as Richeese, Nabati Cheese Wafer, and Korean Goguma, have become household names in Indonesia, synonymous with delicious and affordable snacks.

In addition to its focus on consumer products, Nabati is also involved in the production of food ingredients and seasonings through its subsidiary, PT Kaldu Sari Nabati Indonesia. The company's products are widely used in the foodservice industry, supplying restaurants and food manufacturers with high-quality ingredients.

Nabati Group is a dynamic and forward-thinking company that is committed to providing quality products and services to its customers. With its strong focus on innovation, sustainability, and customer satisfaction, Nabati is poised for continued growth and success in the years to come.
value:
1. Nabati has achieved remarkable success as a leading FMCG company in Indonesia through its unwavering commitment to innovation, sustainability, nutrition, corporate responsibility, employee engagement, and financial performance.
2. The company has consistently introduced innovative and appealing products that have captured the hearts and taste buds of Indonesian consumers, establishing popular brands like Richeese Nabati Cheese Wafers, Richoco Nabati Chocolate Wafers, and Nabati Crackers. Its global expansion and product diversification have solidified its position as a leader in the snack food industry.
3. Nabati prioritizes sustainable practices throughout its operations, ensuring environmental responsibility through the use of sustainable palm oil and eco-friendly packaging solutions. The company also demonstrates its commitment to nutritional advancement by developing healthier food options with reduced sugar, fewer calories, and higher amounts of fiber.
4. Nabati's active involvement in community development initiatives and its partnerships with various organizations reflect its dedication to corporate social responsibility and environmental stewardship. The company also fosters a positive and supportive work environment, investing in employee engagement and talent development programs to enhance employee skills and career growth.
5. Nabati's consistent financial growth and market expansion, along with its leading position in the Indonesian snack food market, demonstrate its ability to adapt to changing market trends and consumer preferences. These achievements are a testament to Nabati's unwavering commitment to excellence and its dedication to providing delicious, nutritious, and sustainable food options for consumers worldwide.

name: BCA
description:
Bank Central Asia (BCA), officially known as PT Bank Central Asia Tbk, is the largest private bank in Indonesia with a significant presence in the nation's financial sector. Established in 1957, BCA has grown steadily over the years, becoming a cornerstone of Indonesia's economic development. Today, BCA boasts an extensive network of over 1,600 branches and 18,000 ATMs across the country, serving millions of individual and corporate customers.

BCA's comprehensive range of banking products and services caters to diverse needs, encompassing retail banking, corporate banking, treasury and international banking, and wealth management. The bank's commitment to innovation has led to the development of cutting-edge digital banking solutions, including mobile banking and internet banking platforms, providing customers with convenient and secure access to their finances.

BCA's success is built on a foundation of strong corporate governance, sound risk management practices, and a customer-centric approach. The bank is committed to social responsibility, actively supporting various initiatives that promote education, healthcare, and environmental sustainability. As Indonesia's largest private bank, BCA plays a pivotal role in driving financial inclusion and contributing to the nation's economic growth and prosperity.
value:
1. Financial Performance and Market Leadership: BCA consistently delivers strong financial performance, reflected in its robust profitability and asset growth. The bank maintains a leading position in the Indonesian banking sector, with a significant market share in deposits, loans, and other financial services.
2. Innovation and Digital Transformation: BCA has been at the forefront of innovation in the Indonesian banking industry, embracing digital technologies to enhance customer experience and operational efficiency. The bank's mobile banking app, BCA mobile, is one of the most popular and highly rated apps in Indonesia, offering a wide range of features and services.
3. Extensive Branch Network and ATM Coverage: BCA boasts an extensive network of branches and ATMs across Indonesia, ensuring convenient access to banking services for its customers. The bank's presence in both urban and rural areas reflects its commitment to financial inclusion and serving the diverse needs of its customer base.
4. Award-Winning Customer Service: BCA has consistently received recognition for its excellent customer service, demonstrating its dedication to providing a positive and seamless experience for its customers. The bank has won numerous awards for its customer service initiatives, including the "Best Customer Service Bank" award from Infobank.
5. Commitment to Sustainability and Social Responsibility: BCA is committed to sustainable practices and social responsibility, integrating environmental and social considerations into its business operations. The bank has implemented various initiatives to reduce its environmental impact, support sustainable development, and contribute to the well-being of the communities it serves.
6. Strong Corporate Governance and Risk Management: BCA maintains a robust corporate governance framework and adheres to high standards of risk management, ensuring the integrity and stability of its operations. The bank has received recognition for its sound corporate governance practices and its commitment to risk mitigation.
7. Employer of Choice and Talent Development: BCA is recognized as an employer of choice, attracting and retaining top talent through its commitment to employee development and career growth. The bank invests in training programs, mentorship initiatives, and a positive work culture to foster a high-performing workforce.
8. Contribution to Indonesia's Economic Development: BCA plays a significant role in Indonesia's economic development, providing financial services that support businesses, entrepreneurs, and individuals across the country. The bank's contributions have helped drive economic growth and improve the lives of Indonesians.
9. Global Recognition and Awards: BCA has received international recognition for its achievements, consistently ranking among the top banks in Indonesia and Asia. The bank has been awarded by prestigious institutions like Forbes, FinanceAsia, and Asiamoney for its financial performance, innovation, and corporate governance practices.
10. Legacy of Excellence and Continuous Growth: BCA has established a legacy of excellence, consistently delivering value to its customers, shareholders, and the communities it serves. The bank continues to grow and innovate, adapting to changing market dynamics and maintaining its position as a leading force in the Indonesian banking landscape.

name: Astra International
description:
Astra International is a leading diversified conglomerate in Indonesia with a strong presence in various sectors, including automotive, agribusiness, heavy equipment, mining, energy, financial services, information technology, and infrastructure & logistics. Founded in 1957, Astra has grown into a formidable business empire, becoming one of the largest listed companies on the Indonesia Stock Exchange (IDX) with a total market capitalization of over seven percent.

Astra's automotive business is its core strength, holding a significant share of the Indonesian market through its partnerships with renowned brands such as Toyota, Daihatsu, Isuzu, UD Trucks, Peugeot, and BMW for automobiles, and Honda for motorcycles. Astra also has a strong presence in the automotive component sector through its subsidiary PT Astra Otoparts Tbk.

In addition to its automotive dominance, Astra has expanded its reach into other sectors, demonstrating its adaptability and strategic foresight. The company's agribusiness division, PT Astra Agro Lestari Tbk, is a major player in the palm oil industry, while its heavy equipment and mining division, PT United Tractors Tbk, is a leading distributor of Caterpillar products. Astra's financial services arm, PT Astra Sedaya Finance Tbk, provides a comprehensive range of financial solutions, and its information technology subsidiary, PT Astra Graphia Tbk, offers a diverse portfolio of IT services.

Astra International's commitment to sustainability is evident in its environmental initiatives, such as its adoption of energy-efficient practices and its support for renewable energy projects. The company also actively engages in social responsibility programs, focusing on education, healthcare, and community development.
value:
1. Leading diversified conglomerate in Indonesia with strong presence in various sectors
2. Founded in 1957 and has grown into a formidable business empire
3. One of the largest listed companies on the Indonesia Stock Exchange (IDX) with a total market capitalization of over seven percent
4. Core strength lies in the automotive business, holding a significant share of the Indonesian market
5. Partnerships with renowned brands like Toyota, Daihatsu, Isuzu, UD Trucks, Peugeot, BMW for automobiles, and Honda for motorcycles
6. Strong presence in the automotive component sector through its subsidiary PT Astra Otoparts Tbk
7. Expanded reach into other sectors, demonstrating adaptability and strategic foresight
8. Major player in the palm oil industry through its agribusiness division, PT Astra Agro Lestari Tbk
9. Leading distributor of Caterpillar products through its heavy equipment and mining division, PT United Tractors Tbk
10. Provides a comprehensive range of financial solutions through its financial services arm, PT Astra Sedaya Finance Tbk
11. Offers a diverse portfolio of IT services through its information technology subsidiary, PT Astra Graphia Tbk
12. Committed to sustainability through environmental initiatives like energy-efficient practices and support for renewable energy projects
13. Actively engages in social responsibility programs, focusing on education, healthcare, and community development

name: Garuda Food Indonesia
description: GarudaFood is a major food and beverage company based in Indonesia, founded by Sudhamek AWS and his wife, Helianti Hilman, in 1990. GarudaFood started as a home-based snack business and has grown into one of Indonesia's prominent food and beverage companies. GarudaFood is particularly renowned for its peanut-based products, including roasted peanuts, peanut butter, and peanut-flavored snacks. Even so, it also offers a variety of biscuits, snacks, and chocolate-based products under different brand names. These products cater to different consumer preferences and include sweet and savory snacks. While initially focused on the Indonesian market, GarudaFood has expanded its presence internationally. Its products are available in several countries, contributing to the company's global footprint.

name: Acer Inc
description:
Acer Incorporated, often simply referred to as Acer, is a Taiwanese multinational technology company specializing in hardware and software development and sales. Founded in 1976, Acer is one of the world's leading producers of personal computers, tablets, smartphones, and displays. The company is headquartered in New Taipei City, Taiwan, and has employees in over 100 countries and territories.

Acer's products are sold under its own brand name, as well as under various sub-brands, such as Predator, Nitro, and Aspire. The company's products have been praised for their value for money and their innovative design. Acer has been a major player in the personal computer market since the 1990s, and has consistently ranked among the top three PC vendors in the world. In recent years, Acer has expanded its product portfolio to include smartphones, tablets, and displays. The company has also been investing heavily in research and development, and is committed to developing new and innovative products.

Acer is a global company with a strong presence in all major markets. The company is committed to providing its customers with high-quality products and services at an affordable price. Acer is a leading innovator in the technology industry, and is committed to developing new and exciting products that meet the needs of its customers.
value:
1. TIME Best Inventions 2023: Acer was named one of Time magazine's Best Inventions of 2023 for its SpatialLabs™ Touch technology, which enables stereoscopic 3D content on laptops without the need for specialized glasses. This breakthrough technology has the potential to revolutionize the way people interact with digital content.
2. Taiwan Excellence 2024: Acer received the prestigious Taiwan Excellence Award in 2024 for its Veriton Vero series of eco-conscious desktops. These desktops are made from recycled materials and feature energy-efficient designs, aligning with Acer's commitment to sustainability.
3. Good Design Award 2023: Acer garnered the prestigious Good Design Award in 2023 for its Swift X OLED laptop. This laptop was praised for its sleek design, powerful performance, and long battery life.
4. Red Dot Winner 2023: Acer received several Red Dot Awards in 2023, including Brand & Communication Design, Digital Solutions, Packaging Design, Interface Design, and Web Design. These awards recognize the company's excellence in various aspects of product design and marketing.
5. COMPUTEX 2023 Best Choice Award: Acer was presented with the Best Choice Award at the 2023 Computex Taipei trade show for its Predator Orion X gaming desktop. This award acknowledges the desktop's exceptional performance and innovative features.
6. Webby Winner 2023: Acer's website was honored with a Webby Award in 2023, a prestigious recognition for outstanding website design and user experience.
7. Webby People's Voice Winner 2023: Acer's website was also recognized as a Webby People's Voice Winner in 2023, a testament to its popularity and positive user feedback.
8. iF Design Award 2023: Acer received an iF Design Award in 2023 for its eco-friendly mouse and Predator gaming headset. These products were praised for their sleek design, sustainable materials, and ergonomic features.
9. BIG Innovation 2023: Acer's Project Chiron, a concept laptop with a foldable screen, was awarded the BIG Innovation Award in 2023. This award recognizes innovative and groundbreaking designs in the technology industry.

name: Kraft Heinz
description:
The Kraft Heinz Company is a global food and beverage company formed by the merger of Kraft Foods Group, Inc. and H.J. Heinz Company in 2015. The company is co-headquartered in Chicago, Illinois, and Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.

Kraft Heinz is one of the world's largest food and beverage companies, with a portfolio of iconic brands including Kraft, Heinz, Velveeta, Oscar Mayer, Planters, and Jell-O. The company has a strong presence in North America, Europe, and Latin America, and its products are sold in more than 200 countries.

Kraft Heinz is committed to providing consumers with high-quality, affordable food and beverages. The company is also dedicated to sustainability and social responsibility. Kraft Heinz has a number of initiatives in place to reduce its environmental impact and support communities around the world.
value:
1. Brand Diversification: Kraft Heinz has successfully diversified its portfolio of brands to appeal to a wider range of consumers. The company has acquired brands like Oscar Mayer, Planters, and Capri Sun, expanding its presence in categories such as meat, snacks, and beverages.
2. Global Expansion: Kraft Heinz has expanded its global reach to over 200 countries, making its products available to consumers worldwide. The company has established manufacturing facilities and distribution channels in key markets, allowing it to cater to regional preferences and taste profiles.
3. Market Leadership: Kraft Heinz holds a leading position in several categories within the food and beverage industry. The company's iconic brands, such as Kraft Macaroni and Cheese and Heinz Ketchup, are household names and command strong market shares.
4. Sustainability Initiatives: Kraft Heinz is committed to sustainability and has implemented various initiatives to reduce its environmental impact. The company has set ambitious targets to reduce greenhouse gas emissions, water usage, and waste generation across its operations.
5. Social Responsibility Efforts: Kraft Heinz is actively involved in social responsibility initiatives that support local communities and promote positive change. The company has partnered with organizations working on hunger relief, education, and environmental protection.
6. Product Innovation: Kraft Heinz is constantly innovating its product offerings to meet the evolving needs and preferences of consumers. The company has introduced new flavors, formats, and packaging for its existing brands, while also launching innovative new products to capture new market segments.
7. Digital Transformation: Kraft Heinz has embraced digital technology to enhance its operations and engage with consumers. The company has implemented digital platforms for e-commerce, customer relationship management, and supply chain management.
8. Employee Engagement: Kraft Heinz prioritizes employee engagement and fostering a culture of diversity, equity, and inclusion. The company has implemented programs to recognize and reward employee achievements, and has created a supportive work environment that promotes employee well-being.

name: Paragon
description:
Paragon Technology and Innovation is an Indonesian beauty company founded in 1995. The company is committed to creating innovative and high-quality beauty products that cater to the needs of Indonesian consumers. Paragon has a portfolio of over 30 brands, including Wardah, Make Over, Evos, and Biokos.

Paragon is a leading player in the Indonesian beauty industry, with a strong presence in both the mass and prestige segments. The company's products are sold in over 100,000 retail outlets across Indonesia. Paragon is also expanding its international presence, with products available in countries such as Malaysia, Vietnam, and Thailand.

Paragon is committed to innovation and research and development. The company has a team of over 100 scientists and researchers who are constantly developing new products and technologies. Paragon is also committed to sustainability and social responsibility. The company has implemented a number of initiatives to reduce its environmental impact and support communities around the world.
value:
1. Wardah: Paragon's flagship brand, Wardah, is the #1 halal cosmetics brand in the world with a presence in over 15 countries. Wardah has been recognized for its high-quality products, wide range of offerings, and commitment to halal standards.
2. Make Over: Make Over is a prestige cosmetics brand that caters to the needs of young and trend-conscious Indonesians. Make Over has been praised for its innovative products, stylish packaging, and effective marketing campaigns.
3. Evos: Evos is a gaming and esports lifestyle brand that has partnered with leading esports athletes and teams. Evos has a strong following among young Indonesians and is expanding its product offerings to include apparel, accessories, and esports-themed products.
4. Biokos: Biokos is a premium skincare brand that offers natural and science-backed products. Biokos has been recognized for its effective formulas and commitment to using natural ingredients.
5. International expansion: Paragon is expanding its international presence and has established a strong foothold in Southeast Asia. The company's products are now available in countries such as Malaysia, Vietnam, and Thailand.
6. Innovation: Paragon is committed to innovation and has a strong track record of developing new products and technologies. The company has a team of over 100 scientists and researchers who are constantly working on new formulations and packaging solutions.
7. Sustainability: Paragon is committed to sustainability and has implemented a number of initiatives to reduce its environmental impact. The company has set ambitious targets to reduce its carbon footprint and water usage.
8. Social responsibility: Paragon is committed to social responsibility and has partnered with organizations that support education, community development, and environmental protection. The company also supports initiatives that promote gender equality and empowering women in the beauty industry.

name: Trans 7
description:
Trans7 is an Indonesian free-to-air television network owned by Trans Media, a part of Trans Corp, which in turn a subsidiary of CT Corp.

Founded in 2006, Trans7 is one of the most popular television networks in Indonesia, with a varied programming lineup that includes news, sports, entertainment, and documentaries. The network has a strong presence in the Indonesian market, with a network of over 100 transmitters and a reach of over 100 million viewers.

Trans7 is known for its innovative and creative programming. The network has a number of popular shows, including "Lapor Pak!", "Trans7 Movie Box", "Sport 7", and "MotoGP". Trans7 is also committed to providing high-quality news coverage. The network's news team is one of the largest in Indonesia, and its news programs are consistently ranked among the most watched in the country.

Trans7 has been recognized for its achievements with a number of awards, including the Indonesia Television Awards and the Panasonic Awards. The network is also a member of the Asia Vision Network, a regional television network that promotes cooperation and exchange among Asian broadcasters.

In addition to its television broadcasting business, Trans7 also has a number of other businesses, including a production company, an advertising agency, and a digital media company. The network is a major player in the Indonesian media industry, and its businesses employ thousands of people across the country.

Trans7 is committed to providing high-quality entertainment and information to Indonesian viewers. The network's innovative programming and strong brand recognition have made it one of the most popular television networks in the country. Trans7 is well-positioned for continued growth and success in the years to come.
value:
1. Varied Programming and Reach: Trans7 offers a diverse programming lineup that caters to a wide range of Indonesian viewers, including news, sports, entertainment, and documentaries. The network's extensive reach spans over 100 million households across the country, making it one of the most popular television networks in Indonesia.
2. Innovative and Creative Content: Trans7 is known for its innovative and creative programming, consistently introducing groundbreaking shows that resonate with viewers. The network's popular programs include "Lapor Pak!", a sketch comedy show, "Trans7 Movie Box", a movie block, "Sport 7", a sports news program, and "MotoGP", the premier motorcycle racing championship.
3. News Leadership and Excellence: Trans7 is committed to providing high-quality news coverage, employing a large team of journalists and producing award-winning news programs. The network's news programs consistently rank among the most watched in Indonesia, earning recognition for their in-depth reporting, accurate information, and engaging presentation.
4. Industry Recognition and Awards: Trans7 has garnered numerous awards for its outstanding achievements in the television industry. The network has received accolades from the Indonesia Television Awards, the Panasonic Awards, and the Asian Television Awards, solidifying its reputation as a leading media provider.
5. Digital Media Engagement: Trans7 has embraced digital technology to connect with audiences beyond traditional television viewership. The network's digital platforms, including social media channels, online streaming services, and digital applications, provide interactive experiences and expand the reach of Trans7's content.
6. Community Engagement and Social Responsibility: Trans7 is actively involved in community engagement initiatives and social responsibility programs that support various causes, including education, healthcare, and environmental protection. The network's philanthropic efforts demonstrate its commitment to making a positive impact on society.
7. International Expansion: Trans7 is expanding its presence beyond Indonesia, establishing partnerships and collaborations with television networks in other Southeast Asian countries. This expansion strategy aims to reach a wider audience and share the network's unique brand of entertainment and information with global viewers.

name: PLN
description:
The history of PT PLN (Persero) began on October 27, 1945, when President Soekarno formed the Electricity and Gas Bureau, which was under the Ministry of Public Works and Power, to manage the power plant that was owned at that time with a total capacity of 157.5 MW.

The company developed through several phases of changing forms until 1994, when, according to PP No. 23/1994, it became a limited liability company (Persero), PT Perusahaan Listrik Negara, or abbreviated as PT PLN (Persero), based on deed 169 dated July 30, 1994, from Notary Sutjipto.

As the business environment changes, at the end of 2022, PLN became a holding company overseeing four subholdings engaged in primary energy, generation, and beyond kWh while continuing to foster other subsidiaries.
value:
1. PLN is the largest electricity company in Southeast Asia and the 10th largest in the world.
2. PLN has a monopoly on the distribution of electricity in Indonesia.
3. PLN serves over 81 million customers, accounting for over 99% of the country's electricity supply.
4. PLN's electrification rate is over 99%, one of the highest in the developing world.
5. PLN has made significant progress in increasing renewable energy generation in recent years. In 2022, renewable energy accounted for over 20% of PLN's total generation capacity.
6. PLN is also a major player in the development of the smart grid in Indonesia.

name: Bank Rakyat Indonesia (BRI)
description:
With over 120 years of experience, Bank BRI constantly provides ease and speed in response to the customer’s various demands. Backed by superior banking services, Bank BRI manages millions of customer transactions non-stop 24/7 through service facilities spread across the country.

In line with the nation’s growth, Bank BRI continues to dynamically innovate to fulfill all of the banking customer’s needs while, at the same time, consistently determined to become the main partner for Indonesians to develop the economy.
value:
1. Bank BRI is the largest bank in Indonesia by assets and the second largest bank in Southeast Asia.
2. Bank BRI has a network of over 14,000 branches and over 500,000 ATMs across Indonesia.
3. Bank BRI serves over 125 million customers, accounting for over 40% of the country's banking market share.
4. Bank BRI is a major player in the development of financial inclusion in Indonesia. In 2022, over 90% of Bank BRI's customers were micro, small, and medium enterprises (MSMEs).
5. Bank BRI is also a leader in the development of digital banking in Indonesia. In 2022, over 90% of Bank BRI's transactions were conducted digitally.

name: Bank Mandiri
description:
PT Bank Mandiri (Persero) Tbk or Bank Mandiri, headquartered in Jakarta, is the largest bank in Indonesia in terms of assets, loans and deposits. Total assets as of 2022, were 1.992 Trillion rupiah (around US$133 Billion). As of 2022, Bank Mandiri is the largest bank in Indonesia by total assets.

As of December 2022, the bank had 2,364 branches spread across three different time zones in Indonesia and 7 branches abroad, about 13,027 Automatic Teller Machines (ATMs), and 11 subsidiaries, such as: Mandiri Sekuritas, Mandiri Tunas Finance, AXA Mandiri Financial Services, Bank Mandiri Taspen, and Mandiri AXA General Insurance.
value:
1. Bank Mandiri's assets grew to Rp 551.9 trillion by December 2011, with a 15.6% CAGR since 2006.
2. Loans increased by 22% (CAGR) to Rp 314.4 trillion, and net profit rose by 38.3% (CAGR) to Rp 12.2 trillion during the same period.
3. It's the largest bank in Indonesia, both in assets and as a lender on a consolidated basis.
4. The bank holds Rp 422.3 trillion in third-party funds and maintains a robust asset quality with NPL ratios at 2.21% and 0.52%.
5. A rights issue in February 2011 strengthened the capital base to Rp 62.7 trillion, making it the first Indonesian bank with international status.
6. Subsidiaries contribute 12% to the total consolidated net profit.
7. Bank Mandiri has the largest ATM network in Indonesia (10,000 units) and is recognized for corporate governance.

name: Telkom Indonesia
description:
Telkom Indonesia is the largest telecommunications company in Indonesia and one of the largest in Southeast Asia. It is a state-owned enterprise that provides a wide range of telecommunications services, including fixed-line and mobile telephony, broadband internet, and pay-TV. Telkom Indonesia also plays a major role in the development of the digital economy in Indonesia.

Telkom Indonesia was established in 1965 and has since grown to become a leading provider of telecommunications services in Indonesia. It has a network of over 160,000 base transceiver stations (BTS) and over 10 million kilometers of fiber optic cable. Telkom Indonesia serves over 170 million customers, accounting for over 60% of the Indonesian telecommunications market share.

Telkom Indonesia is committed to empowering Indonesia's digital transformation. It invests heavily in digital infrastructure and services, and its vision is to become the leading digital ecosystem company in Southeast Asia. Telkom Indonesia's values are customer-centricity, innovation, agility, collaboration, and trustworthiness.

5. Telkom Indonesia is a major player in the development of the digital economy in Indonesia. In 2022, 6. Telkom Indonesia invested over US$1 billion in digital infrastructure and services.

name: Bank Negara Indonesia (BNI)
description:
Bank Negara Indonesia (BNI) is the largest bank in Indonesia by assets and the second largest bank in Southeast Asia. It is a state-owned bank that provides a wide range of banking services, including retail banking, corporate banking, and investment banking. BNI also plays a major role in the development of the digital economy in Indonesia.

BNI has over 1,500 branches and over 19,000 ATMs across Indonesia. It serves over 70 million customers, accounting for over 15% of the Indonesian banking market share. BNI is a major player in the development of financial inclusion in Indonesia. In 2022, over 50% of BNI's customers were micro, small, and medium enterprises (MSMEs). BNI is also a leader in the development of digital banking in Indonesia. In 2022, over 80% of BNI's transactions were conducted digitally.

BNI is committed to providing its customers with the best possible service and products. It is also committed to developing innovative and reliable ICT solutions to empower Indonesia's digital transformation. BNI is a leading bank in Indonesia and is playing a vital role in the country's economic development.

name: Air Asia
description:
AirAsia is a Malaysian low-cost airline headquartered in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. It is the largest airline in Southeast Asia by passengers carried and fleet size. AirAsia operates scheduled domestic and international flights to over 130 destinations in Asia, Australia, and the Middle East.

AirAsia is known for its low fares, innovative onboard services, and friendly cabin crew. The airline has won numerous awards for its service and innovation, including the World's Best Low-Cost Airline by Skytrax for 14 consecutive years and the World's Leading Low-Cost Airline Cabin Crew by the World Travel Awards for seven consecutive years.

AirAsia is committed to providing its customers with the best possible flying experience. The airline offers a variety of services and amenities to its passengers, including low fares, innovative onboard services, friendly and attentive cabin crew, and a wide range of destinations to choose from.
value:
1. World's Best Low-Cost Airline: AirAsia has been voted the World's Best Low-Cost Airline by Skytrax for 14 consecutive years, from 2009 to 2023.
2. World's Leading Low-Cost Airline Cabin Crew: AirAsia has been awarded the World's Leading Low-Cost Airline Cabin Crew by the World Travel Awards for seven consecutive years, from 2016 to 2023.
3. Largest Low-Cost Airline in Southeast Asia: AirAsia is the largest low-cost airline in Southeast Asia by passengers carried and fleet size.
4. Most On-Time Airline in Asia Pacific: AirAsia was awarded the Most On-Time Airline in Asia Pacific by Cirium in 2022.
5. Top 4 Most On-Time Airlines in the World: AirAsia was ranked among the top 4 most on-time airlines in the world by OAG in 2022.

name: Mayora
description:
Mayora is one of the leading consumer goods companies in Indonesia. It produces a wide range of products, including biscuits, candies, wafers, chocolates, coffee, and nutritional products. Mayora's products are exported to over 90 countries around the world.

Mayora is committed to providing its customers with high-quality products and to contributing to the social and economic development of Indonesia. The company has a number of programs in place to support the environment and the communities in which it operates. For example, Mayora has planted over 1 million trees in Indonesia and has donated millions of dollars to support education and healthcare programs.

Mayora is a company with a strong track record of success. It is a leader in the Indonesian consumer goods market and is playing a major role in the country's economic development.
value:
1. The Most Prominent Consumer Goods Company in Indonesia in the Ajang Prominent Award 2023
2. Indonesia's Top Brand Award in the Biscuit, Candy, and Wafer categories for over 20 years
3. The Most Admired Companies in Indonesia by Fortune Indonesia for 10 consecutive years
4. The Best Corporate Financial Awards by CNBC Indonesia for its strong financial performance

name: Indosat
description: Indosat IM3, officially known as PT Indosat Multimedia Mobile (Indosat-M3 or IM3), is a prominent telecommunications service provider in Indonesia. Established on July 25, 2001, IM3 was initially created to operate a nationwide GPRS network, a first of its kind in the country. In 2003, Indosat, the parent company, underwent a merger with its three subsidiaries—Satelindo, IM3, and Bimagraha—and subsequently emerged as a comprehensive mobile network operator
value:
Spectrum Holdings and 5G Launch: Following the merger with Three (3) in September 2021, IM3 acquired substantial spectrum holdings, including 30 MHz of B1, 30 MHz of B3, and 10 MHz of B8 spectrum. This enhancement facilitated the launch of 5G services in June 2021 using refarmed n3 (1800 MHz) spectrum, marking a significant step in the advancement of mobile technology in Indonesia​​.

Awards at the Asian Experience Awards 2022: IM3 was honored with two prestigious awards under the Telecommunications category at the Asian Experience Awards 2022. These awards were "User Experience of the Year" and "Indonesia Customer Experience of the Year," reflecting the brand's commitment to providing exceptional customer experiences and services​​.

Recognition at the Selular Awards 2014: Indosat IM3 celebrated significant achievements at the 2014 Selular Awards, a notable event organized by Global Selular Media Group. The company won the "Best Prepaid Card" award for its IM3 Card, highlighting its widespread appeal and service quality to Indonesia's younger generation. Additionally, IM3's commitment to social responsibility and innovation was recognized with the "Best CSR Program" award for the Indosat Wireless Innovation Contest (IWIC). This contest has fostered more than 2,000 innovative telecommunication technology applications, underscoring Indosat's focus on encouraging creative and entrepreneurial skills among Indonesian youth​​.

name: RCTI
description: RCTI (Rajawali Citra Televisi Indonesia): RCTI is one of Indonesia's leading television networks, providing a diverse range of entertainment and informative content to a broad audience. Established in 1989, RCTI has become a prominent player in the Indonesian media landscape, offering a mix of local and international programming, including popular dramas, reality shows, and news broadcasts.

name: DuPont
description: DuPont, formally known as E. I. du Pont de Nemours and Company, is a renowned American conglomerate founded in 1802. With a rich history spanning over two centuries, DuPont has played a pivotal role in various industries, particularly in the fields of chemistry, materials science, and agriculture. The company is widely recognized for its pioneering innovations, including the development of synthetic materials like nylon and Teflon, as well as significant contributions to the advancement of crop protection and genetically modified organisms (GMOs) in agriculture. DuPont's enduring legacy includes a strong commitment to research and development, sustainability, and global outreach, making it a prominent figure in the world of science and industry.
value: Over the years, DuPont has achieved numerous milestones and breakthroughs. Some of its most notable achievements include the invention of nylon in 1935, revolutionizing the textile industry and contributing to the development of various consumer products. In 1967, DuPont introduced the world to Teflon, a non-stick material widely used in cookware. The company has also made substantial contributions to agriculture through innovations in seed technology, crop protection, and biotechnology, improving crop yields and food security. DuPont's commitment to sustainability has led to the development of environmentally friendly products and practices, reinforcing its position as a leader in responsible corporate citizenship. These achievements have solidified DuPont's reputation as a global innovator and problem solver in multiple industries.

name: PT. Astra Otoparts Tbk.

Established in 1976, it has grown to become one of the leading automotive component manufacturers in Indonesia and Southeast Asia. Astra Otoparts plays a crucial role in supporting the automotive industry by supplying high-quality components to both domestic and international markets, contributing significantly to the growth of the Indonesian automotive sector.
value: Some of the notable achievements of PT. Additionally, Astra Otoparts has received recognition for its corporate social responsibility efforts, contributing to the community and promoting sustainability in its operations, which further solidifies its reputation as a responsible and forward-thinking automotive component manufacturer.

name: GoJek
description: Gojek, founded in 2010 in Jakarta, Indonesia, started as a ride-hailing and delivery platform but has since evolved into a super app offering a wide range of services. It provides users with convenient access to transportation, food delivery, shopping, digital payments, and various on-demand services all in one app. Gojek's platform connects millions of customers with a vast network of drivers, merchants, and service providers across Southeast Asia. It has become a prominent player in the technology and digital economy space, reshaping the way people in the region access essential services and contributing significantly to the growth of the gig economy.
value: Some of Gojek's notable achievements include its rapid expansion across multiple Southeast Asian markets, becoming a unicorn company with a valuation of over $10 billion, and playing a pivotal role in promoting financial inclusion through its digital wallet, GoPay. Gojek's services have positively impacted the livelihoods of countless gig workers, making it a significant player in the gig economy. Additionally, the company has been at the forefront of sustainable transportation initiatives and has made strides in promoting environmental consciousness through its various transportation options.

name: Mustika Ratu
description: Mustika Ratu is a well-known Indonesian cosmetics and herbal skincare company with a strong focus on traditional beauty remedies and wellness products. Mustika Ratu's commitment to using natural ingredients and sustainable practices has earned it a loyal customer base, both in Indonesia and internationally.

name: Exxon Mobil
description: Exxon Mobil Corporation, commonly known as ExxonMobil, is an American multinational corporation headquartered in Irving, Texas. It is a result of the merger of Exxon Corporation and Mobil Corporation in 1999. This company involved itselfs in various aspects of the oil and gas industry, including exploration, production, refining, and marketing of petroleum products. The company operates globally and has a presence in nearly every facet of the energy sector. In the downstream sector, ExxonMobil is involved in refining crude oil into petroleum products and marketing these products. This includes fuels, lubricants, and other petrochemical products. ExxonMobil operates in numerous countries and regions around the world, including Indonesia. It has a significant footprint in the Americas, Europe, Asia, and Africa.

name: MAP
description: Mitra Adiperkasa (MAP) is a leading lifestyle retailer in Indonesia with over 3,200 retail stores and a diversified portfolio that includes sports, fashion, department stores, kids, food & beverage and lifestyle products. Incorporated in 1995, MAP achieved phenomenal growth over the years culminating in its IPO in November 2004. Some of its iconic brands include Starbucks, Zara, Marks & Spencer, SOGO, SEIBU, Oshkosh B’Gosh, Converse, among many others. MAP has a significant presence in the sports and active lifestyle segment. It manages various sports and outdoor brands, catering to consumers with an interest in fitness and outdoor activities.

name: RCTI
description: RCTI, or Rajawali Citra Televisi Indonesia, is one of Indonesia's leading private television networks, owned by PT Media Nusantara Citra Tbk (MNC Group). RCTI was established on August 24, 1989, and it officially began its broadcast on August 24, 1989 as the Indonesia's first private television station. MNC Group has interests in television, radio, print media, online media, and other sectors. RCTI is a national television station that broadcasts a variety of programs, including news, entertainment, dramas, reality shows, and sports. It has a broad audience base and is known for producing and broadcasting popular content. RCTI has expanded its reach beyond Indonesia and can be accessed by viewers in neighboring countries and has been recognized for its international presence.
